com.cloudera.cdk.data
Class PartitionKey

java.lang.Object
  com.cloudera.cdk.data.PartitionKey

@NotThreadSafe
public class PartitionKey
extends Object

A key for retrieving partitions from a Dataset.

A PartitionKey is a ordered sequence of values corresponding to the FieldPartitioners in a PartitionStrategy. A PartitionKey may be obtained using PartitionStrategy.partitionKey(Object...) or PartitionStrategy.partitionKeyForEntity(Object).

Implementations of PartitionKey are typically not thread-safe; that is, the behavior when accessing a single instance from multiple threads is undefined.

See Also:
PartitionStrategy, FieldPartitioner, Dataset
